… as Abba Kyari staff also join victims  Governor Bala Mohammed of Bauchi State has tested positive for coronavirus. This was disclosed by his Senior Special Assistant on Media, Mukhtar Gidado, in a statement on Tuesday. The governor had gone into self isolation after revealing that he met and shook hands with the son of former Vice President Atiku Abubakar, Mohammed, who tested positive for COVID-19 on Sunday. Meanwhile, there is palpable fear at the Presidential Villa as three staff of the Chief of Staff to the President, Abba Kyari, test positive for COVID-19. Kyari had tested positive for the virus. A source at the Presidency, who confirmed the development to our correspondent, added that all the aides at the Vice President’s wing, except his media aide, did not report for work on Monday. The Villa appears to be on a gradual lockdown, our correspondent observed. 